                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(etco) #iiv(erso) #142v" facs="001 003 145"/>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, col. 1, upper</locus>
                    “Praise and glory to God who helped me to finish in health and peace, amen, in 1956 E.C., on the tenth of Säne” (= April 18, 1964 C.E.)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, col. 1, lower (in blue)</locus>
                    This book belongs to Märä(?) Kǝbrät.  The copyist is Ḥarägä Wäyn of the land of Tǝgre. The owner is willing this book to his “learned child.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, column 2, bottom (black and red ink)</locus>
                    List of the family of the owner of the manuscript
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#79v" facs="082"> f. 79v, column 3</locus>
                    Will relating to a list of other books he owns. These include books of Ziq, Four Gospels, Psalter, Anqäṣ of Dǝggwa, Ṣoma Dǝggwa, Ziq [again], two copies of Horologium for the Night Hours, and one book of Genesis. Written on Ṭǝqǝmt 10, 1970 E.C.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#141r" facs="143"> f. 141r, col. 2</locus>
                    “Finished the Book of Mǝ‘raf of the Fasting Period with the peace of God on twentieth of Mäskäräm, in the year of Matthew the Evangelist, 1957 E.C.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#141r" facs="143"> f. 141, col. 2</locus>
                    “There was no rain in 1977 [E.C.] until the day of Raphael” [which is at the end of the year]
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    marginal notation throughout, some of which may be overlooked text
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 6–7
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24v #32v #44v #48r" facs="027 035 047 050"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12v #124r" facs="015 126"/>);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#131r" facs="133"> f. 131r, col. 1, line 8</locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#20r #22v" facs="022 025"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
